"""
Investment Weekly

Fed Expected to Lower Interest Rates Amid Inflation Challenges
Key Event: December 16 - 20, 2024

U.S. CPI: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) rose by 2.7% YoY in November, up from 2.6% in October, while the Producer Price Index (PPI) adjusted to 3.0% YoY, up from 2.6%. This shows a moderate trend in inflation levels.

Fed Policy: The Federal Reserve is expected to cut interest rates at its meeting on December 17–18. CME Group’s FedWatch Tool indicates a 96% probability of a 0.25% rate cut, reflecting strong market expectations for easing monetary policy.

Investment Perspective
The Fed's interest rate decision and ongoing monetary easing are likely to influence market dynamics. This presents opportunities in markets that may benefit from easing inflationary pressures and rising asset prices.

Market Updates
International Stocks: PMI data and key reports from December 16–17 will be critical ahead of the Fed's decision. Rate policy announcements from the Bank of Japan (BoJ) on December 18–19 are also expected to affect markets.

Thai Stocks: Domestic stocks may see support from foreign fund inflows, especially in sectors poised for growth amid a changing interest rate environment.

Gold: Gold prices remain stable without significant changes. Investors are awaiting cues from monetary policies and global economic trends.

Oil: Oil prices are pressured by weak demand and oversupply. Recent IEA reports and OPEC's adjustments may influence oil markets heading into 2025.

Core-Satellite Portfolio Strategy
80% Core: Multi-Asset Funds (e.g., K-WPBALANCED, K-WPSPEEDUP, K-WPULTIMATE).
